wiki.text:
'FPV' may refer to:
* Federació de Pilota Valenciana, Valencian Pilota Federation.
* Feline panleukopenia virus a virus affecting cats, minks and ferrets.
* First Person View, or Flight Per Video, a method of piloting radio-controlled
  aircraft or UAVs using a wireless video camera.
* Fishery Protection Vessel of the Scottish Fisheries Protection Agency.
* Ford Performance Vehicles, the Melbourne-based, premium performance vehicle
  partner of automobile manufacturer Ford Australia.
* Front for Victory, a political party and alliance in Argentina.
